author: AP
title: Esterline Technologies misses Street 3Q forecasts
text:
BELLEVUE, Wash. (AP) _ Esterline Technologies Corp. (ESL) on Thursday reported fiscal third-quarter earnings of $28.5 million.
On a per-share basis, the Bellevue, Washington-based company said it had profit of 92 cents. Earnings, adjusted for non-recurring costs and to account for discontinued operations, were $1.33 per share.
The results fell short of Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of four analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of $1.47 per share.
The aerospace and defense supplier posted revenue of $496.2 million in the period, also falling short of Street forecasts. Four analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $531.4 million.
Esterline Technologies shares have fallen 25 percent since the beginning of the year. In the final minutes of trading on Thursday, shares hit $81.92, a decrease of 30 percent in the last 12 months.
